channel.title: Making a Auxy Wiki?
channel.description:
I mentioned this idea based on the [Auxy Sound Wiki](https://disco.auxy.co/t/auxy-sound-wiki/10012) thread but a wikia.com wiki for auxy? it would have info on sounds, update history, prominent producers and other info like that.
If a bunch of people are interested in this id be down to get one started
Edit: the wiki is auxy.fandom.com

This thread is confusing. Where is the actual wiki site? Is it the fandom page?

item.title: Making a Auxy Wiki?
item.dc:creator: HYDRANS
item.description:
I think having specific producers is a bad idea, especially if it’s a wiki, because people are just going to want to add their own page and there is no fair way to determine which producers get a page (even though there are some good choices).

I do think song links would be fine, especially if they are in context with another topic (like how song examples were used in the Auxy Sound Wiki thread)

TL;DR: Creating a wiki is pointless if it’s just going to become a place where people try to promote themselves

Read full topic

item.title: Making a Auxy Wiki?
item.dc:creator: Arimyth
item.description:
HXGN:

prominent producers

I’d agree with what @stereofield said. (By the way, I think this is a great idea and props to everyone that’s making this happen )

Since Auxy is currently a community of its own as well as an app I think this section especially deserves focus. These are a few that I can name that I think deserve a place on the wiki as ambassadors for Auxy that would also potentially showcase the app’s capability and draw in new users (please feel free to add on to this):

@stereofield for his work with Frontier and being an almost universally known name around here
@foryou, @Thrashie for their work with vvvvv and unique style
@anon38751485 for being a notable example of what’s possible when pushing the boundaries of Auxy
@MisterMaster for his dedication to running the community and heading the Auxy Disco
@blackocean for using Auxy to its full capability and launching himself into other music communities
I don’t know how this would fit on the wiki but I think it’s awesome how @iammane incorporates Auxy into a broader (purely mobile btw) workspace
@aUstin_Haga for being a long term staple name of the community and embodying a consistent flow of professionally crafted music

Feel free to use them or not depending on how much of a priority you feel this element of the wiki is.

Read full topic
